He may very probably have been the Owen Lloid mentioned in Le Neve’s Fasti as arch- deacon of Cornwall 1466-7, chancellor of Exeter in 1467, as collated to the archdeaconry of Earum (Barn- staple) 10 Dec.‚ 1477, and to the archdeaconry of Totnes on 15 Feb„ 1478.
